http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: The Annotation Objects ontology aims to model the annotations and comments made during a renovation project with respect to specific building elements, spaces, etc.
A list of bitmaps can be used to add more information, for example, text in the visualization.
Represents the type of camera being used in the viewpoint.
Clipping Planes can be used to define a subsection of a building model that is related to the topic. Each clipping plane is defined by Location and Direction.
Their purpose is to record discussion between different parties related to the topic.
Represents a coordinate in 3 dimensions.

Lines can be used to add markup in 3D. Each line is defined by three dimensional Start Point and End Point. Lines that have the same start and end points are to be considered points and may be displayed accordingly.
Represents an orthogonal camera being used in the viewpoint.
Represents an perspective camera being used in the viewpoint.
Stage of the topic such as Planning, Construction, etc.
Topic contains reference information of the topic.
Label of the topic, such as Electrical, Architecture, Structural, etc.
Status of the topic such as Open, In Progress, Closed, etc.
Type of the topic such as Comment, Issue, Request, etc.
The viewpoint from which the BIM model is being viewed in the modeling tool.
The user to whom this topic is assigned to. Recommended to be in email format.
Indicates the camera direction of the viewpoint.
Indicates the camera up vector.
Indicates the camera viewpoint direction.
Large description of the comment.
Indicates the creator of the entity.
Indicates the creation date of the entity.
Provides a description of the topic.
Date until when the topics issue needs to be resolved.
Camera’s field of view angle in degrees.
Explicit property to relate a topic to an specific part of the BIM Model.
Relates a viewpoint with a bitmap element.
Relates a viewpoint with the camera being used.
Relates a viewpoint with a clipping plane used to define a subsection in the building model.
Relates a topic with a comment.
Related a viewpoint with the building elements it is conformed.
Indicates a direction given by a 3D world coordinate.
Links a topic to extra document references, such as additional payloads, or links.
Link a topic with internal or external files such as BIM models, videos, images, text, etc.
Connects a viewpoint with a line being used to add markups in 3D.
Indicates the location of the bitmap, specifically the center of the bitmap in 3D world coordinates.
Relates to an specific point in 3D world coordinates.
External references that help complemente the topic in discussion.
Relates a topic with its stage.
Relates a topic with its label.
Relates a topic with its status.
Relates a topic with its type.
Relates a comment with a viewpoint.
Attribute to uniquely identify the topics, comments and viewpoints.
Number to maintain the order of the topics.
Indicates who modified the entity.
Indicates the last time the entity was modified.
Indicates the normal direction of the bitmap.
Topic priority.

Relates a topic to a building.
Relates a topic to an element.
Relates a topic to a project.
Relates a topic to a space.
Relates a topic to a storey.
Relates a topic to another topic.
Filename of the snapshot taken under a viewpoint.
Title of the topic.
Indicates the up direction of the bitmap.
Scaling from view to world.
Name of the viewpoint.
X component of a 3D coordinate.
Y component of a 3D coordinate.
Z component of a 3D coordinate.
